== Instance Methods

--- font

    Gets the selected Gtk::Font.
     * Returns: The selected Gtk::Font

--- font_name

    Gets the Name of the selected font.
     * Returns: Name of the selected font

--- font_name=(font_name)

    Sets the Name of the selected font.
     * font_name: Name of the selected font
     * Returns: font_name

--- label_font_size

    Gets the Font size for label in font info mode.
     * Returns: Font size for label in font info mode

--- label_font_size=(label_font_size)

    Sets the Font size for label in font info mode.
     * label_font_size: Font size for label in font info mode
     * Returns: label_font_size

--- mode

    Gets the mode of operation of the font picker.
     * Returns: The mode of operation of the font picker

--- mode=(mode)

    Sets the mode of operation of the font picker.
     * mode: The mode of operation of the font picker
     * Returns: mode

--- preview_text

    Gets the Preview text shown in the dialog.
     * Returns: Preview text shown in the dialog

--- preview_text=(preview_text)

    Sets the Preview text shown in the dialog.
     * preview_text: Preview text shown in the dialog
     * Returns: preview_text

--- ref_accessible

    See Atk::Implementor#ref_accessible.

--- set_font_name(font_name)

    Same as font_name=.
     * font_name: Name of the selected font
     * Returns: self

--- set_label_font_size(label_font_size)

    Same as label_font_size=.
     * label_font_size: Font size for label in font info mode
     * Returns: self

--- set_mode(mode)

    Same as mode=.
     * mode: The mode of operation of the font picker
     * Returns: self

--- set_preview_text(preview_text)

    Same as preview_text=.
     * preview_text: Preview text shown in the dialog
     * Returns: self

--- set_show_size(show_size)

    Same as show_size=.
     * show_size: Show size in font info mode
     * Returns: self

--- set_title(title)

    Same as title=.
     * title: The title of the selection dialog box
     * Returns: self

--- set_use_font_in_label(use_font_in_label)

    Same as use_font_in_label=.
     * use_font_in_label: Use font in the label in font info mode
     * Returns: self

--- set_widget

     * Returns: self: ((*FIXME*))

--- show_size=(show_size)

    Sets the Show size in font info mode.
     * show_size: Show size in font info mode
     * Returns: show_size

--- show_size?

    Gets the Show size in font info mode.
     * Returns: Show size in font info mode

--- title

    Gets the title of the selection dialog box.
     * Returns: The title of the selection dialog box

--- title=(title)

    Sets the title of the selection dialog box.
     * title: The title of the selection dialog box
     * Returns: title

--- use_font_in_label=(use_font_in_label)

